episodes.title: The Kiss of Freedom
episodes.plot: Out of prison yet again, Ricky and Julian are free and rich after making a large dope sale to the guards and inmates.

episodes.title: Temporary Relief Assistant Trailer Park Supervisor
episodes.plot: Randy is suspended by Barb Lahey, entitling Ricky to the new position of temporary relief assistant trailer park supervisor.

episodes.title: If I Can't Smoke and Swear. I'm Fucked
episodes.plot: Julian has a new plan that involves committing many small crimes so they can't go to jail, and saving the money for a cruise.

episodes.title: Who's the Microphone Assassin?
episodes.plot: The boys put on a rap concert in celebration of J-Roc's new album. Things begin to go awry when J-Roc is caught masturbating.

episodes.title: Closer to the Heart
episodes.plot: When Randy and Lahey rip the boys off on buying Rush tickets, Ricky "borrows" guitarist Alex Lifeson for access to the concert.

episodes.title: Where in the Fuck Is Randy's Barbeque?
episodes.plot: Ricky makes a plan to get rich by using kids to help him steal barbecues.

episodes.title: The Delusions of Officer Jim Lahey
episodes.plot: It's the anniversary of Mr. Lahey's being fired from the police force.

episodes.title: A Shit Leopard Can't Change Its Spots
episodes.plot: When he realizes that he has no ticket for the upcoming cruise and is being evicted from the trailer park, Ricky is determined to go back to jail.
